FBIS3-20347 "drweu061_j_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-061 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Ciampi To Remain in Office Until Speakers Appointed LD2903171694 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1658 GMT 29 Mar 94 LD2903171694 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Language: Italian Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] The government will resign when Prime Minister Ciampi resigns "after the new speakers of both chambers of parliament are elected." This was explained by Antonio Maccanico, undersecretary to the prime minister. [passage omitted]
